p.e:
OCTOBER THE 1ST

MOVED TO THIS ISLAND TO GET
AWAY FROM MY TROUBLES IN
THE CITY.

"RAVENSWICH ISLE" -- A NAME
MOST INTRIGUING. RAVENS DO
ABOUND.

THE LOCALS ARE FRIENDLY, BUT
NOT FORTHCOMING. ODDLY HERE,
NO ONE IS OUT COME EVENING,
ABSOLUTELY EVERYONE RETIRES
TO THEIR HOMES, DOORS LATCHED
AND LOCKED FIRMLY, EVEN GATES
DRAWN BETWEEN ALLEYWAYS.

--AARON WINCHESTERSON

THE SEWERS UNDER RAVENSWICH!

DEEPER DOWN IN THE PIPES...
I JUST SAW SOMETHING IN THEM...
I... I CANNOT QUITE COMPREHEND
WHAT IT WAS!

IT SMELLED ALMOST SWEET AND
BITTER AT ONCE.  THE COLOR WAS
ALMOST AS IF OUT OF SPACE.

I STILL FEEL DISCOMBOBULATED
AND HAVE LOST TRACK OF TIME.

WHAT IS THAT CREEPING BEHIND
ME NOW WHICH VANISHES WHEN
I TURN TO CHECK??

--A.W.

HAUNTED! THE
WOODS HAVE A
TRAIL TO THE CHURCH,

AND THIS EVE WITH A FULL MOON
IT IS STILL...
            FRIGHTFULLY...
                                DARK.

A LANTERN IS A NECESSITY.
SHINING LIGHT LIKE THE BRIGHT
ILLUMINATION OF KNOWLEDGE.

BUT FROM WHAT I HAVE SEEN THUS
FAR. . .

--A.W.

THE EYES.
THE EYES ARE KEY.
BUT WHAT DO THE KEYS UNLOCK?
I NEED MORE SIGHT.
MORE INSIGHT.

PERHAPS AT THE LIBRARY I MAY
LEARN MORE.

THE MOON. IS IT REAL?
IT IS... NOT RIGHT.  WHY AM I
SEEING IT LIKE THIS?
WHAT HAS HAPPENED TO ME?

--A.W.
